{
  "type": "PrimaryTheme",
  "number": 5672,
  "title": "concubines",
  "comment": "A woman, often a servant or slave, with whom a man had regular sexual relations, but to whom he was not married. A concubine did not have the rights of a wife and her children were not rightful heirs, though a wife might offer a servant to her husband as a concubine to have children on her behalf.",
  "refgroup": null,
  "children": [],
